body:
My finished OOAK doll!!

I used a monster high draculara with the legs of this Even After High Raven Queen I had customer but got ruined in storage.

I was trying hard to stick to the concept but just didn’t have the materials nor patience, lol. But I’m super proud on how this came out!! If there’s any suggestions for the next project shoot me an idea!

Also bonus gif

summary: Very early look at my DnD character, Carlisle Bennet! He’s a Sad Mad Dad looking for his kidnapped daughter! He’s a self taught...
caption:
Very early look at my DnD character, Carlisle Bennet! He’s a Sad Mad Dad looking for his kidnapped daughter! He’s a self taught monk of the drunken style.

He was a high ranking officer in a long time religious war. He was sent home after a couple years of service since things were starting to calm down and he needed to go back and see his family. He had a wife and 4 kids (3 boys and 1 girl.) However, he came home to find his family murdered and a note left stating that a cult known as the  Hounds of Nullis had his youngest daughter, Rosie. In his rage and depression, he took to drinking and bar fights to try and find information from anyone about this cult. Now 35, he’s been tailing this cult for years but hopes that with his newly found party… he can finally find his daughter again and try to regain some sense of normalcy.

hello guys!! I’ve recently opened commissions on insta and twitter for may/june and I still have some slots available! send me a dm through chat (no asks, they sometimes fail to reach through) or email at kingdeino@virgilio.it if you’re interested!

More infos/rules:

- payment upfront via PayPal
- no nsfw, no heavy gore (light nude and light gore are acceptable), no real people
- I do ocs of every kind, especially fantasy based ; dnd; pokèmon; the arcana; fanart in general
- I have the right to turn down a commission I don’t feel comfortable with
- I’m an artist with a personal artstyle, so please don’t ask me to imitate other artist’s
- feel free to ask me anything if you have any doubts, im happy to help!
